place_description: Seattle-based coffeehouse chain known for its signature roasts, light bites and WiFi availability.

reviews_data.review_text: Amazing customer service.  Even with system down, crew was very nice and polite. Food always good.
Buena atencion con mi hija. Lo recomiendo.

The baristas here need some basic training on customer relations. I went in and no one says anything or even give glimpse until I literally pressed in on the window to get an eye contact. I had already placed my order on the mobile order and wanted to use the restroom but it has a keypad and sign that says for paying customers only. I went up to the barista to ask for the code, they said it's for paying customers and that I have to order or else I can't use. I told her I already ordered, then she didn't even know the code and gave me a wrong code. Which I had to go back and forth until one of them finally knew the right code. After I used the restroom, my order wasn't even ready and I waited another 5 mins. Meanwhile, new customers coming in but they won't acknowledge a person until someone actually went up to them and asked if they could be helped. I have never been to a Starbucks that a customer had to actually ask for help to get service. This will be first.

I'm a traveling salesman.  I purchased food and drink from 3 Starbucks today but when I went into this one to use the restroom they wouldn't allow me until I purchased something from this store.  Even though I showed them my purchases elsewhere today on my Starbucks App.  They refused to give me the rest room code!  This policy is foolish and greedy!   Time to start using other coffee shops!

There was a worker in there that would not acknowledge me. I was asking for the restroom and she seemed deaf. No response very rude. She has a nose piercing, Hispanic, she really brought the atmosphere down in this Starbucks. The other gentleman thankfully was very polite and helpful. Good coffee.

I've been to this Starbucks location numerous times and the experience has been subpar, however, the young lady that serviced me today was truly exceptional. I had placed a mobile order and due to certain circumstances I was unable to pick it up. A few hours later when I arrived at this store, I asked one of the baristas if they would mind remaking my drink, seeing as I hadn't been able to pick it up before, and they had already tossed it out. I won't name names because I don't want them to get in trouble, however, the barista gave me a very ugly look and told me they would ask their manager. I'm not entirely sure why they had to do that, but I digress. The manager on duty, her name was Morgan, stopped what she was doing, came over and listened to me explain what had happened, and had zero problems remaking my drink for me. They seemed quite busy, but she prioritized my drink, wrote my name, and even drew a little smiley face on my cup! That small gesture made my entire day. She also made a very good flat white. She was great! Be like her!
This place is poorly managed. Unprofessional employees and drinks made incorrectly, dirty interior and some serious negative attitudes. They need better leadership.

I am a frequent visitor to this Starbucks location and have always enjoyed excellent service. However, my experience today was deeply disappointing.

I waited in the drive-thru for over 25 minutes without my order being taken--10 of those minutes were spent at the speaker box. After waiting patiently, I eventually said "hello?" only to be met with a curt response: "Yeah, um, we're busy!" I continued to wait, but there were no visible cars ahead of me for quite some time. Meanwhile, I could see three cars behind me, clearly frustrated, stuck in a line we couldn't leave.

When I decided to leave after waiting too long, I turned the corner and saw a car being served at the window. To my surprise, it appeared that several cars had been served while no new orders were being taken. I pulled up and politely asked to place my order, explaining that I had been in line for over 20 minutes. The staff member at the window, however, told me, "Unfortunately no, you'll need to go around."

I expressed how unfair this felt, but my concerns were dismissed. When I asked to speak to a manager, Morgan arrived with the same indifferent attitude. I asked for the staff members' names and left.

This experience left me questioning why I was treated so poorly. I visit this location several times a week and work within a mile of it. Normally, my visits are pleasant, but today's experience has made me reconsider returning.

I understand that situations arise where staff may be overwhelmed or understaffed, but the lack of communication, empathy, and customer service today was unacceptable.

Went inside to order coffee and use restroom. Restroom doors were locked. There were four people behind the counter. There was someone before that said she had already been waiting. I waited 10 mins.. one barista walked to the back and didn't acknowledge us. The other 3 baristas just stared us even when asking a question and just kept working the drive thru and mobile orders. The inside long became so long and still no help. I don't know the management or workflow style but they can do so much better, I left. I line that only had 2 people in it became even longer for an inside that wasn't too busy.
